Devon, She/Her, Asexual, In a state of sustained fear.
I draw stuff. Blog features material that is almost always tagged appropriately unless I mess something up. 
Commissions are currently [closed] and I do not schedule when they re-open so I cannot give you a time frame for that. Askbox is usually open for doodle suggestions,headcanons, questions, what have you. 
READ BEFORE SENDING MESSAGES!
_Please only suggest things for fandoms I have shown recent interest in. I don't plan out my interests so questions about old fandoms and if I plan to draw for them are not appreciated. I am NEVER looking for new fandoms to get into, please DO NOT suggest new series for me, I promise you I HAVE heard already, I'll mention it on my own if I care. 
FEMALE FOCUS KINK ART IS BY COMMISSION ONLY AND NOT APPRECIATED WHEN SUGGESTED!!!
 ABSOLUTELY NO PERSONAL KINK STORIES! I am massively uncomfortable with irl fetish stories from people.
Even tho I am marked as an NSFW blog I do not enjoy sex based suggestions and would appreciate if you didn't leave them. I do not like pregnancy based kinks at all and I will not draw them or discuss them.Don't ever end a message in "Thanks in advance" because I will not draw for it under implied obligations.
I am not here to teach you the intricacies of my sexuality. If you do not understand it do your own basic research instead of violating the privacy of a complete stranger. I am not my kink, do not treat me as a character.

blog.name: professor-hemlock
blog.description: Hello,my name is Honor Hemlock, and I'm a Pokemon Scientist! The world is teeming with prospect and mystery just waiting to be discovered, and that's exactly what me and my team intend to do! I've followed all the notes I could left behind by the late Dr Fuji, and what little was left of his research after the Mewtwo incident, but it's quite the lead. I believe both mew and Mewtwo are still the key to a wealth of understanding that would benefit all life on Earth today. Stay stunned for updates on the journey!

blog.description:
Reviewing my personal opinion on every single Pokemon! Yes, all 809 of them!
(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - The Tynamo Family
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - The Tynamo Family
body:
602: Tynamo

Oh man guys, it’s one of THOSE lines. One of the ones I’ve been just dying to get into. Starting off with the most adorable little blood-sucker out there, the pure Electric Type Tynamo. Surprisingly not packing a Water type as well, Tynamo’s family has the Levitate ability. Making these lampreys monster that swim in the air as well as water. Very dangerous. But very cute.

Personal Score: 8.5/10

A good friend!

603: Eelektrik

Let me just say how happy I am about this line also doubling as the obligatory “electric eel” monster that was inevitable for a series like this. A plain ol’ electric eel could’ve been so dang boring, or passable at best, but they also merged it with the lamprey thing, giving it infinitely more personality than just another cool snake-like fish could’ve done.

Eelektrik’s wide-eyed face and gaping mouth and whole Electric theme just makes the thing lovely. The color scheme is fantastic, love me some bright yellows on dark, navy-blues. The one shame is that you’ll never have an Eelektrik for longer than a few minutes. Tynamo is laughably week, but immediately learns all the moves you need as soon as it evolves into Eelektrik, only needing to wait a few levels for Thunderbolt. And just after that, you can slap a Thunderstone on it and get your Eelektross now. Made even worse with how you get a free Thunderstone right in the same area you find Tynamo in. Whoops.

Personal Score: 8/10

Maybe my least favorite of this line, but still very nice.

604: Eelektross

Now look at how just plain awesome this thing is! While still very eel-ey, we’re still dealing with a Pokemon that is plenty Lamprey. Ey. And what’s creepier than a lamprey? A lamprey that not only swims through the air, but also has arms to grab onto you with. Arms that also seem to be somewhat additional sucker-mouths. Or at least I’d like to think of it that way.

But just about every addition it makes onto Eelektrik is perfect. The beady, red eyes. The cool dorsal fin. That gorgeous color scheme. The cool mouth. The fact that it not only hovers in the air but also makes a goofy waddle on the ground too. What’s not to love about this thing? It’s so cool and adorable in the weirdest way!

My one criticism is that I feel like it’s maybe lost a bit of personality when it made the transition to 3D. Yeah, it hovering makes more sense for its ability, but I feel like there’s something sorely missed in having the thing dance around in its Gen 5 sprite but just sorta hover and swim in the newer games.

Personal Score: 10/10

Overall:

A wonderful trio of friends!

[Archive]

summary: So, this anonymous request inspired me to make all of them. You guys are gonna have to unlock them all in order to see them by...
caption:
So, this anonymous request inspired me to make all of them. You guys are gonna have to unlock them all in order to see them by sending an ask. However, you can only ask for one at a time.  The one with the most asks will be the one that gets revealed. Of course I won’t make a new post for each one, it’ll all be here and I’ll reblog it with each new one.

But yeah. I thought it’d be fun to make them all. All are electric and their respective types.

Vaporchu and Umbrechu

Vaporeon and Pikachu fusion and Umbreon and Pikachu fusion

Vaporchu: Water/Electric Type

Umbrechu: Dark/Electric Type

Abilities: Vaporchu - Static - HA - Water Absorb, Umbrechu - Static - HA - Synchronise

Vaporchu - The Aqua Rodent Pokemon

Umbrechu - The Night Rodent Pokemon

Vaporchu needs to be careful when swimming in water as it can accidentally release small amounts of electricity from its pouches. It swims in a zigzag type of motion. 

Umbrechu scares off its foes by using its electrical marking on its body. It, however, isn’t that aggressive.  But, when it battle, it will taunt people by giving them a small electric shock.
